OL,3,CCould feeding gulls become a finable
OL,4,Coffence?
OL,6,F"A by-law would reduce aggressive
OL,7,Fbehaviour during nesting, protect
OL,8,Fresidents, visitors, and businesses,
OL,9,Fimprove public health and help restore
OL,10,Fnatural gull habitats."
OL,12,FThe by-law would allow council
OL,13,Fofficers to ban feeding gulls in
OL,14,Fdesignated area, and intervene where
OL,15,Fthe behaviour persisted.
OL,17,FScottish Borders Council had in the
OL,18,Fpast engaged in a practice called 'egg
OL,19,Foiling', which stops eggs from
OL,20,Fhatching, and nest destruction to
OL,21,Fcontrol the gull population.
